---
intent: >
  Build the public /brain section as two static-export Next.js routes — Walkthrough at
  /brain (linear §01–§05 guide) and Cookbook at /brain/recipes (3-column rail / recipe /
  sticky generator) — translating the design-handoff JSX into App Router idioms with
  three pure-client interactive surfaces (skeleton generator, config-flow visualizer,
  worked-examples tabs / recipe rail), a brain-section-scoped BRAIN_PAL palette
  extension, a brain-scoped footer line, surgical edits to both top-bar components
  to add a `brain` nav entry adjacent to `docs` with mobile parity, and a slug-gated
  reverse link inside DocsTemplate for /docs/methodology/brain-aide → /brain.
---

## Project Structure

The tree below is the proposed state of `src/app/brain/` after this plan executes,
plus a short list of out-of-scope files this plan modifies in place. Annotations
that say "(new)" are created by this plan; "(modified)" are existing files
edited by this plan; "(unchanged)" are untouched but referenced for context.

