└── _data/                             ← static data tables consumed by interactive surfaces (new)
    ├── backendPresets.ts              ← (new) BACKEND_PRESETS table: `Record<PresetKey, BackendPreset>` where `PresetKey = 'obsidian' | 'filesystem' | 'notion'` (THREE entries only — the JSX BACKEND_PRESETS object holds three) and `BackendPreset = { name: string, command: string, argLines: string[], orientation: string, config: string }`. `argLines` entries starting with `~` render as YAML null with optional inline comment (preserves the JSX's `~  // ← absolute path…` pattern verbatim). Authored character-for-character from brain-shared.jsx lines 65–156. Exports `BACKEND_PRESETS`, `type PresetKey`, `type BackendPreset`.
    ├── workedExamples.ts              ← (new) WORKED_EXAMPLES table consumed by `<WorkedExamples/>` ONLY: `Record<WorkedExampleKey, { label: string, blurb: string, tools: string, orient: string, config: string, args: string }>` where `WorkedExampleKey = 'filesystem' | 'notion' | 'obsidian'`. Distinct shape from BackendPreset because the worked-examples panes show `tools` (one-line) and `args` (preformatted multi-line YAML string), NOT a parsed argLines array. Authored from brain-variant-walkthrough.jsx lines 254–306.
    ├── recipeIndex.ts                 ← (new) RECIPE_INDEX consumed by `<RecipeRail/>`: ordered array of `{ id: RecipeKey, label: string, subtitle: string }` where `RecipeKey = 'quickstart' | 'flow' | 'states' | 'mcp' | 'orient' | 'configsec' | 'fs' | 'notion'` (8 entries, in the exact order from brain-variant-cookbook.jsx lines 8–17). Each entry's `label` and `subtitle` are quoted verbatim. Exports `RECIPE_INDEX`, `type RecipeKey`.
    ├── bootStates.ts                  ← (new) BOOT_STATES: ordered array of `{ id: 'ok' | 'no-brain-aide' | 'no-mcp-entry' | 'mcp-drift', kind: CalloutKind, what: string, fix: string }`. Authored from brain-shared.jsx lines 351–356.
    ├── mcpTools.ts                    ← (new) MCP_TOOLS: ordered array of `{ sig: string, why: string, required: boolean }` for the 5 tool entries. Authored from brain-shared.jsx lines 372–378.
    ├── codeSamples.ts                 ← (new) preformatted code-string constants: `SCAFFOLD_PREVIEW` (Walkthrough §01 right pane, from walkthrough.jsx lines 60–80), `SEED_PREVIEW` (Walkthrough §03 right pane, lines 126–136), `ORIENT_GOOD_SAMPLE` (Cookbook `orient` recipe, cookbook.jsx lines 153–163), `CONFIG_SKELETON_SAMPLE` (Cookbook `configsec` recipe, lines 181–194). Multi-line template literals authored verbatim — whitespace preserved.
    └── brainCopy.ts                   ← (new) load-bearing copy strings: HERO_A_LINE_1, HERO_A_LINE_2, HERO_A_EYEBROW, HERO_A_SUBHEAD, HERO_A_CHECKS (3-tuple), HERO_B_EYEBROW, HERO_B_LINE_1, HERO_B_LINE_2, HERO_B_LINE_3, SECTION_TITLES (§01–§05 phrasing), FOOTER_LINE, FOOTER_TRIO (`github ↗`, `npm ↗`, `discuss`), PAGE_TITLE_A, PAGE_TITLE_B, OG_DESCRIPTION; quoted verbatim from spec hero blocks + handoff §9 + JSX line ranges noted next to each constant; consumers import to avoid drift.
