**Files modified outside `src/app/brain/` (targeted edits, not full rewrites):**

```
src/app/_components/TopBar/index.tsx               ← (modified) add `brain` entry to NAV_LINKS adjacent to `docs`; flip `mobileVisible` so docs+brain remain visible at every viewport
src/app/docs/_components/ActiveAwareTopBar/
  index.tsx                                        ← (modified) extend ActivePage union with 'brain'; map any pathname starting with /brain to active='brain'
src/app/docs/_components/DocsTemplate/
  DocsTemplate/index.tsx                           ← (modified) when route.section === 'methodology' && route.slug === 'brain-aide', render a reverse-link banner ("→ tutorial: wire your own backend") between Breadcrumb and H1
src/app/sitemap.ts                                 ← (modified) append /brain/ and /brain/recipes/ entries (priority 0.7)
src/app/globals.css                                ← (modified) append a single `:where(.brain-pal) { --color-accent2: #7aa6d6; --color-warn: #d6b25a; --color-bad: #c25a3a; --color-good: #8cbe5a; }` rule. Tokens exist only on `.brain-pal` descendants — no global leak.
```

**Files NOT modified (in scope by user direction):**

- `.aide/intent.aide` — root spec lag is waived per spec.
- `.aide/docs/brain-aide.md` — package-vendored markdown ships unchanged; reverse link is injected by the docs template.
- DocsSidebar / docs sidebar nav — no `# BRAIN` section added.

## Prerequisites

This plan depends on the following existing modules' contracts. They are already
in place and unchanged by this plan; they must continue to expose the same
contracts when this plan executes.

- `@/app/_components/TopBar` must continue to export a default `TopBar` component
  whose source contains a `NAV_LINKS` array with `{ label, href, external,
  mobileVisible }` entries. Step 8 modifies this array in place.

- `@/app/docs/_components/ActiveAwareTopBar` must continue to export a default
  client component that derives the active TopBar entry from `usePathname()`.
  Step 9 extends its `ActivePage` discriminator union and prefix-matching block.

- `@/app/docs/_components/DocsTemplate/DocsTemplate` must continue to receive
  `{ route: DocRoute, frontmatter, commit, published, renderedHtml, prev, next }`
  and render Breadcrumb → H1 → DocMeta → body → PrevNext → DocsFooter. Step 10
  inserts a slug-gated banner element between Breadcrumb and H1.

- `@/service/docsRegistry` must continue to walk `.aide/docs/` under section
  `methodology` and produce a route whose `(section, slug)` is
  `('methodology', 'brain-aide')` and whose `urlPath` is
  `/docs/methodology/brain-aide`. Steps 4 and 5 hard-link to the registry-emitted
  URL `/docs/methodology/brain-aide/` (with trailing slash, per
  `next.config.mjs`'s `trailingSlash: true`).

- `@/app/globals.css` must continue to declare the existing `--color-bg`,
  `--color-card`, `--color-fg`, `--color-dim`, `--color-border`, `--color-accent`
  tokens at the `@theme` layer. Step 2 appends a `:where(.brain-pal) { … }`
  block alongside without modifying any existing tokens.

## Plan

### 1. Author static data tables and the copy registry

Read: `coding-playbook/architecture/folder-structure`, `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions`

This step lands the load-bearing data-only modules every later step will import.
All six tables are colocated in `src/app/brain/_data/` because nothing outside
the brain section consumes them. Each constant is authored character-for-
character from the named JSX module — do not paraphrase, do not normalize
whitespace, do not collapse multi-line template literals. The implementor must
read the cited JSX line ranges before writing any string.

- [x] Create `src/app/brain/_data/brainCopy.ts` exporting these constants
      (sources: `design-handoff/brain-variant-walkthrough.jsx` for HERO_A,
      `design-handoff/brain-variant-cookbook.jsx` for HERO_B, handoff §9 for the
      §01–§05 titles + footer, `design-handoff/handoff.md` §4 for OG strings):

      `HERO_A_EYEBROW = "# a guide for backend authors"` (walkthrough.jsx line 23)
      `HERO_A_LINE_1 = "wire any backend"` (walkthrough.jsx line 25)
      `HERO_A_LINE_2 = "as a brain."` (walkthrough.jsx line 26 — second line is
      dimmed via `text-[color:var(--color-dim)]`)
      `HERO_A_SUBHEAD` — verbatim from walkthrough.jsx lines 28–33; renders with
      an inline accent-colored span around `brain.aide`. Text:
      `"The brain.aide file is a plugin interface. It tells AIDE how to launch
      your storage backend over MCP and how to talk to it once it's live.
      Bundled today: an Obsidian default. This page walks you through wiring
      that default, then shows you how to author your own — a Notion brain, a
      flat-filesystem brain, anything that can speak MCP."` Implementor renders
      this as a `<p>` with a single inline `<span>` around `brain.aide`.
      `HERO_A_CHECKS` — 3-tuple `["5-step walkthrough", "3 worked examples",
      "live skeleton generator"]` (walkthrough.jsx lines 35–37)
      `HERO_B_EYEBROW = "# brain.aide cookbook"` (cookbook.jsx line 36)
      `HERO_B_LINE_1 = "recipes for the "` (cookbook.jsx line 38; trailing space)
      `HERO_B_LINE_2 = "brain"` (cookbook.jsx line 38; renders inside an inline
      accent-colored span)
      `HERO_B_LINE_3 = " plugin interface."` (cookbook.jsx line 38; leading
      space + trailing period)
      `HERO_B_SUBHEAD_LINES` — 2-tuple of comment-style lines from cookbook.jsx
      lines 41–42:
      `["# pick a recipe from the rail. each one stands alone — no need to
      read top-to-bottom.", "# the skeleton generator on the right stays sticky
      so you can experiment as you read."]`
      `SECTION_TITLES = { '01': 'install + scaffold the default', '02': 'wire
      it: /aide:brain config', '03': 'seed the entry-point artifacts', '04':
      'verify with the boot reporter', '05': 'build your own backend' }` (per
      handoff §9 + walkthrough.jsx lines 44, 87, 107, 143, 150)
      `SECTION_SUBHEADS = { '01': '# the cli writes .aide/config/brain.aide
      pre-filled with the obsidian template.', '02': "# the config flow has
      two paths. the one that runs depends on what's in args.", '03': '# the
      four seed sections in brain.aide become four files inside your brain.',
      '04': '# at session start the orchestrator checks brain.aide vs
      .mcp.json. four states.', '05': '# everything above worked with bundled
