### 2. Extend the global CSS palette with a BRAIN_PAL scope rule

Read: `coding-playbook/foundations/anti-patterns`, `coding-playbook/setup/tailwind-v4-gotchas`

Spec contract: BRAIN_PAL must NOT enter the `@theme` block (would expose tokens
site-wide). Playbook contract: no CSS Modules, no CSS-in-JS, no `style={{}}`
when Tailwind arbitrary values work. The reconciliation: a single
`:where(.brain-pal) { … }` rule appended to `globals.css` declaring the four
custom properties on the `.brain-pal` descendant scope only. Brain components
consume them via Tailwind arbitrary-value classes
(`bg-[color:var(--color-warn)]`, `text-[color:var(--color-good)]`, etc.) — no
component CSS files, no inline styles, full conformance with the
Tailwind-only rule. The `:where(...)` selector keeps specificity at zero so
existing palette tokens still cascade naturally.

- [x] Append a single CSS block to `src/app/globals.css` (after the existing
      `@theme` block, before the keyframes block):

      `:where(.brain-pal) {
         --color-accent2: #7aa6d6;
         --color-warn: #d6b25a;
         --color-bad: #c25a3a;
         --color-good: #8cbe5a;
       }`

- [x] Do not modify any existing rule, do not touch `@theme`, do not introduce
      a new file under `src/app/brain/`. The only required change is the append
      to `globals.css`. Verify by inspection: the four hex values appear
      nowhere else in the project.

### 3. Build the brain-section primitives

Read: `coding-playbook/client/components`, `coding-playbook/architecture/folder-structure`

Static, layout-neutral building blocks reused across Walkthrough and Cookbook.
Most are server components; CopyChip and CmdLine are clients because they own
clipboard state. Each primitive follows the project component convention:
PascalCase folder + `index.tsx` default export, JSDoc on the export,
`className` accepted on the outermost element only and merged via the existing
`cn` helper at `@/lib/cn`. JSX line refs below resolve every prop and behavior.

- [x] Create `_components/primitives/Card/index.tsx` — bordered card matching
      the docs callout border treatment; props:
      `{ children: ReactNode, className?: string }`. Server component.
- [x] Create `Eyebrow/index.tsx` — uppercase 11px letter-spaced label colored
      `text-[color:var(--color-accent)]`; props:
      `{ children: ReactNode, className?: string }`. Server component.
- [x] Create `Chip/index.tsx` — pill `<button>` used both as backend-preset
      selector (filled accent bg + dark `#0d0b08` text when active, transparent
      bg + foreground text when inactive) and as horizontal tab. Renders as
      `<button>` for accessibility (do NOT use `<div role="button">` — the
      JSX uses `<button>` for these throughout, see brain-shared.jsx line 226
      and brain-variant-walkthrough.jsx line 313). Props:
      `{ active?: boolean, onClick?: () => void, ariaLabel?: string,
      children: ReactNode, className?: string }`. Server component (the click
      handler is passed in by the parent client component).
- [x] Create `CopyChip/index.tsx`. Top of file: `'use client'`. Props:
      `{ text: string, label?: string, className?: string }`. State:
      `copied: boolean`. On click: writes `text` to `navigator.clipboard`,
      sets `copied=true`, swaps the rendered label to `✓ copied`, resets to
      the prior `label` (default `⧉ copy`) after ~1400ms via a `setTimeout`
      whose handle is cleared on unmount in a `useEffect` cleanup. JSX source:
      brain-shared.jsx lines 21–29 (note: JSX uses 1400ms; preserve that
      timing, NOT the 1500ms the prior plan said). Renders as a `<button>`
      with `cursor: pointer`; never as a `<span>` (the JSX uses `<span>` but
      the playbook requires `<button>` for click targets — see Decisions).
- [x] Create `CmdLine/index.tsx`. Top of file: `'use client'`. Props:
      `{ cmd: string, className?: string }`. State: `copied: boolean`. The
      ENTIRE box is clickable (matching JSX brain-shared.jsx lines 31–47);
      renders as `<button>` with appropriate role + keyboard support so Enter
      and Space activate the click handler. Inside: `$` accent prefix +
      monospace `cmd` body + trailing `⧉` (idle) / `✓` (copied) indicator.
      Border-left 2px in `--color-accent`. Do NOT compose CopyChip here — the
      whole-row click target requires a single `<button>` element, not an
      inner button-in-button.
- [x] Create `CodeBlock/index.tsx` — replaces the JSX's `CodePre` (brain-
      shared.jsx lines 49–62). Props:
      `{ code: string, label?: string, maxHeight?: number, className?: string }`.
      When `label` is set, renders a header bar with `{label}` on the left and
      a `<CopyChip text={code}/>` on the right; below, a `<pre>` with the
      verbatim `code` content. When `label` is omitted, renders just the
      `<pre>`. Server component (CopyChip is the only client part and is
      composed in).
- [x] Create `Callout/index.tsx` — brain-scoped callout block.
      Props: `{ kind: CalloutKind, label?: string, children: ReactNode,
      className?: string }` where
      `type CalloutKind = 'why-stop' | 'ok' | 'no-brain-aide' | 'no-mcp-entry'
      | 'mcp-drift' | 'success'`. Kind-to-color mapping (extended from prior
      plan to cover the four boot states authoritatively per brain-shared.jsx
      lines 351–356):
      `why-stop` → `--color-warn`;
      `ok` → `--color-good`;
      `no-brain-aide` → `--color-bad`;
      `no-mcp-entry` → `--color-warn` (JSX line 354: warn dot);
      `mcp-drift` → `--color-warn` (JSX line 355: warn dot);
      `success` → `--color-good` (after-restart-and-seed bubble).
      Border-left 2px solid the kind's color (matching JSX `borderLeft: 2px
      solid` everywhere — NOT 3px), uppercase optional label, body in
      `--color-fg`. Do NOT reuse the docs `.callout-*` classes. Server
      component.
- [x] Create `FooterCard/index.tsx` — the spec / RELATED card primitive.
      Props: `{ href: string, cta: string, title: string, body?: string,
      external?: boolean, className?: string }`. JSX source: walkthrough.jsx
      lines 336–345. The `cta` is the small accent-green eyebrow line (e.g.
      `docs/brain-aide.md →`), `title` is the bold body title (e.g. `the
      spec`), `body` is the optional dim sub-prose. When `external === true`,
      renders `<a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">`; otherwise
      renders `<Link>` from `next/link`. Server component.
- [x] No tests for primitives — they are pure render with no logic.

### 4. Build the four pure-client interactive surfaces

Read: `coding-playbook/client/components`, `coding-playbook/foundations/anti-patterns`

The four interactive components — three named in spec/handoff §8 plus the
Cookbook-only `SkeletonCompact` — all carry `'use client'`, hold state via
`useState`, and never fetch. State boundaries: each component owns its own
state (no Context, no global store). The Cookbook rail/body coupling is
handled in the Cookbook orchestrator (step 6), not here. Every prop signature
and state shape below is extracted directly from the JSX source — see line
ranges. JSX-equivalent logic must be matched behaviorally, not transcribed
character-for-character (the JSX uses inline styles + `React.useState`; the
implementor uses Tailwind arbitrary values + the standard `useState` import).

