      `name: string` (default `BACKEND_PRESETS.obsidian.name`),
      `overrideOrient: boolean` (default `false`),
      `orient: string` (default `BACKEND_PRESETS.obsidian.orientation`).
      `useEffect` watches `backend`: on change, sets `name` to the new preset's
      name and (if `!overrideOrient`) refreshes `orient` from the new preset's
      orientation (matches JSX lines 165–168 verbatim). Renders a 2-column grid:
      LEFT — labeled `backend` block with vertical button column (one button
      per `Object.keys(BACKEND_PRESETS)` — three entries); labeled `name
      (label)` text input bound to `name`; `override orientation` checkbox
      bound to `overrideOrient` (when checked, immediately seeds `orient` from
