### 6. Compose the Cookbook variant body

Read: `coding-playbook/client/components`, `coding-playbook/architecture/folder-structure`

The cookbook is structurally interactive — recipe selection in the rail must
swap the body. The sticky-right `SkeletonCompact` is independent (owns its own
backend toggle per the JSX, NOT a parent-driven prop) so the only shared state
is `activeKey: RecipeKey` between the rail and the body. `CookbookShell` is the
single client component holding that state; `RecipeRail` and `RecipeBody`
receive the active key and the handler via props. The outer `Cookbook/index.tsx`
is a server component composing the hero, the shell, and the footer.

JSX-to-component mapping (every block in `brain-variant-cookbook.jsx` maps to a
named component below):

| JSX block (lines)                | Component                              |
| -------------------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| Top bar (lines 22–32)            | (NOT shipped — `<TopBar/>` from layout) |
| Hero strip (lines 34–44)         | `Cookbook/Hero/`                        |
| Rail buttons (lines 49–66)       | `Cookbook/RecipeRail/`                  |
| RELATED rail (lines 67–71)       | `Cookbook/WalkthroughCrossLink/`        |
| Main body (lines 75–77)          | `Cookbook/RecipeBody/`                  |
| Sticky generator (lines 80–83)   | `interactive/SkeletonCompact/` (4b)     |
| Footer strip (lines 86–92)       | (NOT shipped — `<BrainFooter/>` from layout) |
| `<RecipeBody>` switch (97–217)   | `Cookbook/RecipeBody/` (8 branches)     |
| `<P>`/`<Bullet>`/`<C>` (220–233) | `cookbook-blocks/` text helpers         |
| `<Step>` (234–244)               | `cookbook-blocks/Step/`                 |
| `<RecipeWorked>` (246–268)       | `cookbook-blocks/RecipeWorked/`         |

