- [x] 12m. Cross-links resolve: Walkthrough's `<WalkthroughFooter/>` "the
      spec" card 200s at `/docs/methodology/brain-aide/`. Walkthrough's "the
      source" card opens `EXTERNAL_GITHUB_URL` in a new tab. Walkthrough's
      `<CookbookCrossLink/>` 200s at `/brain/recipes/`. Cookbook's
      `<WalkthroughCrossLink/>` exposes three working links: `docs / brain-
      aide.md →` 200s at `/docs/methodology/brain-aide/`, `all canonical
      docs →` 200s at `/docs/`, and `tutorial: wire your own backend →` 200s
      at `/brain/`.
- [x] 12n. DocsTemplate banner: at `/docs/methodology/brain-aide/`, the
      reverse link `→ tutorial: wire your own backend` appears between
      breadcrumb and H1, colored `--color-accent`, and 200s at `/brain/` on
      click. At any other docs route (sample: `/docs/methodology/aide-spec/`),
      the banner is absent.
- [x] 12o. No `href="#"` survives in the rendered output of either /brain
      route. Spot-check by viewing source.
- [x] 12p. BRAIN_PAL containment: viewing `/`, `/docs/`, or any non-brain
      route in DevTools, no element computes `--color-accent2`,
      `--color-warn`, `--color-bad`, or `--color-good`. The four tokens
      resolve only on descendants of the `.brain-pal` wrapper.
- [ ] 12q. JetBrains Mono only: no second typeface anywhere on /brain,
      including code-style frontmatter blocks inside the skeleton generator.
- [x] 12r. OG preview: `https://aidemd.dev/brain/` pasted into a link-preview
      tester (or via `<head>` source inspection) shows title `PAGE_TITLE_A`
      (`brain.aide — wire any backend as a brain`), description
      `OG_DESCRIPTION` (`A guide for backend authors. Wire the bundled
      Obsidian default, then learn how to author your own brain plugin.`),
      and the canonical `og.png` image (inherited per handoff §4 — no
      brain-specific OG image). For `/brain/recipes/`, title is
      `PAGE_TITLE_B` and the same description and OG image apply.
- [x] 12s. Sitemap: `/sitemap.xml` (built via `next build`) includes both
      `https://aidemd.dev/brain/` and `https://aidemd.dev/brain/recipes/`
